UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="accordion__content" id="Why_study_this_degree-1" style="--panel-height: 341px;"> <p>Our Graduate Diploma and Master of Mathematics Education programs are designed to retrain accredited teachers from other disciplines in mathematics as a teaching area. Live online classes provide the opportunity to learn from lecturers and peers as role models of excellent teaching practice, network, ask questions and gain expert advice.</p><p>The programs enable you to develop deep and flexible content knowledge in pure and applied tertiary-level mathematics. They also allow you to develop your mathematics pedagogy and enhance your capacity to engage your students to work mathematically to solve challenging, real-world problems across science, technology, engineering and mathematics (STEM) fields.</p><p>This program will improve your expertise and career prospects. Qualified secondary mathematics teachers are in high demand across Australia. It also fosters transferable skills such as critical reasoning, problem-solving, ethical judgement, and decision-making. The program has been designed around school terms to assist you in balancing existing work, family and other commitments.</p><!-- <p>Aimed at those who are already working in the primary and secondary education field, our Graduate Certificate in Mathematics program enables students to become proficient in pure and applied tertiary-level mathematics. You will also develop skills in analysing problems and developing innovative solutions, using technology to teach and enhance your communication and learning skills.</p> <p>Our part-time program has been specifically designed for working teachers who either want to improve their own mathematical expertise and career prospects or who would like to teach mathematics in the Catholic education system. The program consists of four core courses (Principles of Mathematics, Linear Algebra, Calculus and Statistics) and has been designed around your existing work, family and other commitments.</p>--> </div>',
